# CURSOR-SKILLS - Testing

Source: [cursor-skills/testing](https://github.com/araguaci/cursor-skills/tree/main/testing)

## CURSOR setup

- Jest, Cypress, Testing Library, Coverage Gutters, Test Explorer, Mocha (per project).

## Typical structure

```
project/
├── src/   ├── tests/   ├── coverage/   ├── fixtures/   ├── mocks/
└── .env
```

## Unit

- Isolated, fast tests; clear assertions; mocks for external deps; descriptive names; `jest.autoRun: "off"` if preferred.

## Integration

- Component interaction and data flow; test DB and external services mocked or controlled; setup/teardown; `testing.autoRun: "off"` if preferred.

## E2E

- User journeys; Cypress or similar; page objects; test data and cleanup; `cypress.autoRun: "off"` if preferred.

## Organization and data

- Group by feature; names that describe the scenario; fixtures for data; consistent mocks; coverage ≥ 80% where it makes sense.

## Tools

- Prettier, ESLint; coverage reports; test-case and troubleshooting docs.
